**[Blockonomics.co](https://www.blockonomics.co)** is an easy to use bitcoin financial tracker. It enables users to watch balances/transactions of multiple addresses without requiring private key.

## Features

### Address Watcher

**[Blockonomics.co](https://www.blockonomics.co)** provides a address watcher. User can add public bitcoin [[addresses|Address]] and also label them using tags. Dashboard shows a quick overview of balances classified by each tag

### Transaction History
[[transactions|Transactions]]
As of December 10th 2013, **[Biteasy.com](https://www.biteasy.com)**  has added [testnet](https://www.biteasy.com/testnet/blocks) support to it's Blockexplorer, which now gives you the ability to easily switch between that and [mainnet](https://www.biteasy.com/blockchain/blocks) as well.

### Notifications

Except the web interface, [developers](https://www.biteasy.com/developers) can access the blockexplorer data (for both Mainnet and [[testnet|Testnet]]) through the **REST API**. The API is *free* to use, but in order to ensure the quality of the service, a global limit has been set. There is also the option to lift that limit through the use API keys which the developer can acquire by [contacting Biteasy.com](https://www.biteasy.com/support) first.

